<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?> <legaldoc><law type="statute"><section><amendatorysection chaptername="Insurance" statutenumber="44-1983"><bookinfo>Reissue Revised Statutes of Nebraska</bookinfo><statuteno>44-1983</statuteno><catchline>Authorized activities of title insurers.</catchline><para>Subject to the exceptions and restrictions contained in the Title Insurers Act, a title insurer shall have the power to:</para><para>(1) Transact only title insurance business; and</para><para>(2) Reinsure title insurance policies.</para></amendatorysection></section><source><para>Laws 1997, LB 53, &#167; 6. </para></source></law></legaldoc> 